TopSpeed Professional TechKit          Release notes version 3.10
=============================          ==========================



KNOWN PROBLEMS IN TOPSPEED TECHKIT
==================================


þ   The post-mortem debugger does not correctly show the value
    of local variables where a program has been terminated by
    an exception, and third-party software has hooked the
    exception vectors in such a way that the BP register is not
    preserved.

þ   The profiler will only operate in line number mode for one
    module at a time.

þ   The resource compiler does not accept NOT as an operator.
    The ~ operator may be used instead. Also, the / character
    is not acceptable in filenames. Use \ instead.


Increasing the maximum file handle count
========================================

To do this you must have the source kit for the appropriate
language(s) as you will to rebuild libraries.

1: Add the following code to INITEXE.A before 'jmp far __startup'

---------------------------------------------------------------------
(* extend handle size *)
  push ax
  mov ah,30H        (* check version >= 3.03 *)
  int 21H
  cmp al,3
  ja $handleextnd
  cmp ah,3
  jb $nohandleextend
$handleextnd:
  mov ax,ds         (* PSP seg into AX *)

  push  bx
  push  es
  mov   es,ax
  mov   bx,ds:[2]   (* recover END-OF-ALLOCATION segment in BX *)
  mov   ax,ds
  sub   bx,ax       (* calculate total program size *)
  sub   bx,11H      (* adjust down 11H paras., 256bytes plus 16 for slack *)
  mov   ah,4AH      (* release this memory back to DOS to handle files *)
  int   21H
  sub   word ds:[2],11H (* decrement END-OF-ALLOCATION value for libraries *)
  pop   es
  mov  ah,67H
  mov  bx,255     (* prepare DOS to handle up to 255 file handles. *)
  int  21H        (* NB value must be odd and < 256 *)
  pop  bx
$nohandleextend:
  pop ax
  jmp far __startup
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. Change OPEN_MAX (default 20) in COREFILE.A to required number of files
   (remember that 5 are reserved by DOS)

3.
   Modula-2
   --------
   Change MaxOpenFiles in FIO.DEF to required value-5
   Change MaxHandles in COREFILE.DEF to required value

   Pascal
   --------
   Change MaxHandles in COREFILE.ITF to required value

   C
   --------
   Change NFDS in DOS.H to required value
   Change HANDLE_MAX in IO.H to required value

4. Remake all appropriate libraries and INITEXE.OBJ.

5. Remember to set FILES= in your CONFIG.SYS and that running on
   some networks you may need to change some configuration information.



